School of Business, Equine and Sport Studies

Midway University is pleased to offer our students and prospective students with the support they need from the time of inquiry through completing your application and understanding the cost of going to Midway.

The application process for all students is relatively the same. There are however different admission requirements for Undergraduate students, Evening and Online students and Graduate students. Visit our Apply to Midway section to understand the process and what information you will need in order to apply for the particular program. There are some programs such as equine studies, nursing and teacher education that also require program specific admittance requirements to be met before acceptance into those programs.

Even before you apply we are happy to discuss the costs and any fees that will apply to earning your degree. Visit our Cost & Aid section of this site to learn about all of our Financial Aid services and detailed costs.

We work hard to keep our costs affordable and still provide a special private, liberal arts education experience at Midway University. You will be surprised at just how affordable a Midway University education can be. More than 90 percent of our students receive some type of financial assistance to bring the cost of a quality education well within reach.

Our friendly and knowledgeable staff in the Financial Aid Office is here to give you the individual attention you need to understand and evaluate all of your financial aid options. We will gladly work with you one-on-one throughout the process of applying for and receiving financial assistance to make your dreams of a Midway education a reality.
